{
  "local_port": 46020,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "What is best steakhouse in San Diego?",
  "response": "San Diego is home to a vibrant culinary scene, and its steakhouses are no exception. Whether you're looking for a classic ambiance, modern twists, or scenic views to complement your meal, San Diego offers a variety of top-notch steakhouses. Here are some of the best steakhouses in the city as of 2023:\n\n1. **Born and Raised**\n   - **Location:** Little Italy\n   - **Highlights:** Born and Raised is renowned for its luxurious Art Deco decor and a wide selection of prime dry-aged steaks. Their menu also features an impressive array of appetizers, from oysters to truffle fries. The rooftop dining area offers stunning views of the city, making it perfect for a special night out.\n   - **Specialties:** Wagyu beef, bone marrow appetizers, craft cocktails.\n\n2. **The Grill at Torrey Pines**\n   - **Location:** Torrey Pines Golf Course, La Jolla\n   - **Highlights:** Nestled within the picturesque Torrey Pines Golf Course, this steakhouse provides not only exceptional dishes but also breathtaking views of the Pacific Ocean. The modern yet cozy interior makes it suitable for both intimate dinners and larger gatherings.\n   - **Specialties:** Prime rib, seafood selections, extensive wine list.\n\n3. **Donovan\u2019s Steak House**\n   - **Location:** Gaslamp Quarter\n   - **Highlights:** A staple in San Diego's Gaslamp Quarter, Donovan\u2019s Steak House offers a classic steakhouse experience with a contemporary touch. The sophisticated ambiance is complemented by top-quality steaks and attentive service.\n   - **Specialties:** Filet mignon, New York strip, handcrafted cocktails.\n\n4. **Nick\u2019s Steakhouse**\n   - **Location:** Downtown and Gaslamp Quarter\n   - **Highlights:** Known for its consistent quality and elegant setting, Nick\u2019s Steakhouse is a favorite among locals and visitors alike. The menu emphasizes locally sourced ingredients, and the wine list is both extensive and thoughtfully curated.\n   - **Specialties:** Ribeye steak, seafood dishes, gourmet sides.\n\n5. **Bourbon Steak by Michael Mina**\n   - **Location:** Banker\u2019s Hill\n   - **Highlights:** Owned by acclaimed chef Michael Mina, Bourbon Steak offers a modern take on the traditional steakhouse. The menu blends classic techniques with innovative flavors, and the stylish interior provides a trendy yet comfortable atmosphere.\n   - **Specialties:** Dry-aged steaks, seafood creations, signature cocktails.\n\n6. **Cowboy Star Restaurant & Butcher Shop**\n   - **Location:** Downtown\n   - **Highlights:** Combining a steakhouse with a butcher shop, Cowboy Star offers a unique farm-to-table experience. They source their own beef, ensuring high quality and freshness. The rustic yet chic decor adds to the overall dining experience.\n   - **Specialties:** House-cut steaks, charcuterie boards, locally sourced sides.\n\n**Choosing the Best Steakhouse for You:**\nThe \"best\" steakhouse can depend on what you're looking for\u2014be it ambiance, specific cuts of meat, wine selections, or additional menu offerings like seafood and appetizers. It's also worth considering the location and whether you\u2019re looking for a more traditional or contemporary dining experience.\n\n**Tips:**\n- **Reservations:** Many of these top steakhouses are popular and can book up quickly, especially on weekends. It's advisable to make reservations in advance.\n- **Dress Code:** While some steakhouses maintain a formal dress code, others might be more casual. Checking ahead can ensure you\u2019re dressed appropriately for your chosen venue.\n- **Special Orders:** If you have specific preferences regarding steak cuts or doneness, most steakhouses accommodate special requests\u2014just communicate them to your server.\n\nEnjoy your dining experience in San Diego!",
